The paper focuses on the collaboration between humans and robots, specifically on the physical interactions between them. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a mathematical approach to improving the robot's ability to exploit human interactions for successful task completion, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the importance of human-robot interaction and cooperation, which suggests that it may belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The validation of the proposed approach through experiments conducted with a humanoid robot suggests that the paper may also belong to the Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on the physical interactions between humans and robots and the proposed approach's potential for improving the robot's ability to complete tasks suggests that the paper may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
